Pre-heat your oven to 200 degrees and bring a #pot{} of water to the boil with 1/2
tsp of @salt{1/2%tsp}(this is for the noodles later on). Mix together the
@oyster sauce{2%tbsp} and the @honey{2%tbsp} and pop the
@pork fillet{2}(sliced) in a #roasting tin{}. Spread your soy honey mixture over
the pork, turning the meat so it is evenly coated. Sprinkle evenly with the
@black sesame seeds{2%tbsp} so the pork has a good covering.

Pop in your oven for ~{20%mins} and when the 20 mins are up, take your pork out
of your oven, cover your roasting tin with #foil{} and pop back in for a further
~{10%mins}.

> Covering the pork with foil prevents the outside burning while still cooking
> the inside of the meat.

While your pork is cooking get the noodles and vegetables prepared! Put the
@noodles{4%servings} in the pot of boiling water for ~{3%mins} then drain them.

> The noodles should be just soft enough to eat, so test them before draining.

Refill the pot with cold water, put the noodles back in and keep the pot to the
side.

> This will stop them cooking and keep them from sticking together.

Now time for the veggies! Chop off the root of the @pak choi{2%heads} and then
chop it widthways into 3cm slices. Peel and chop off the tops and bottoms of
the @carrots{4}(peeled) and then pull a #vegetable peeler{} lengthways along
them, this will make lovely thin ribbons (if you use a knife they would be too
thick).

Put 2 tbsp of @oil{2%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} and add your vegetables along with
@salt{1/2%tsp} and some @black pepper{}. Stir-fry your vegetables for
~{2 1/2%mins}.

Add the @peanut butter{3%tbsp} to a #bowl{} with the @soy sauce{4%tbsp} and
@water{1%tbsp}. Give it a good stir to loosen it up and when your vegetables
have fried for ~{2 1/2%mins}, add the mixture to the pan. Stir-fry for another
~{1%minute} before draining your noodles and adding them to the pan. Stir
everything together gently until it is all combined and heated through.

When your pork is cooked, slice it into 1cm slices, pop your stir fry into a
bowl and serve your pork slices on top. Drizzle a little of the juices from
your pork roasting tin on top and enjoy!